The speeding bus collided with the wall of the church

A speeding bus rammed into a church in Kerala on Saturday, causing the wall of the church to collapse and fall on top of the bus. The bus collided head-on with a car before hitting the wall of the church, which pulverized the car. The video of this incident was captured in the CCTV camera installed on the road, which is now going viral on the social media. The bus that hit the church belonged to the State Transport Corporation (KSRTC). Many people have been seriously injured in this accident.

Bhado Ashaad Chahe Jeth Ke Gham Kehu Bujhe Nahi..!, Neha Singh Rathore | Farmers | 

Another new song of Bhojpuri singer and artist Neha Singh Rathore has been uploaded on YouTube and in this song Neha has shared the pain of the farmers of India.

Neha has uploaded a new song on her channel today whose title is Bhado Ashaad Chahe Jeth Ke Gham Kehu Bujhe Nahi..! In which she is trying to tell about the plight of the food provider of the country i.e. our farmers.

Neha is telling the pain of the farmers of the country through her song, she is telling in her song that even after working hard for the farmers for the whole year, the farmer continues to drown in poverty, any leader or officer of the country does not care for the farmers. Doesn't take care.

Neha is constantly putting the country's governments in the dock through her folk songs and is making the country's condition and problems accessible to every citizen of the country through her folk songs and is constantly questioning the governments.
